    <summary>High level manager used to obtain an instance of an <c><see cref="T:Android.Nfc.NfcAdapter" /></c>.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">High level manager used to obtain an instance of an <c><see cref="T:Android.Nfc.NfcAdapter" /></c>.
 </para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">
 Use <c><see cref="M:Android.Content.Context.GetSystemService(System.String)" /></c>
 with <c><see cref="F:Android.Content.Context.NfcService" /></c> to create an <c><see cref="T:Android.Nfc.NfcManager" /></c>,
 then call <c><see cref="P:Android.Nfc.NfcManager.DefaultAdapter" /></c> to obtain the <c><see cref="T:Android.Nfc.NfcAdapter" /></c>.
 </para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">
 Alternately, you can just call the static helper
 <c><see cref="M:Android.Nfc.NfcAdapter.GetDefaultAdapter(Android.Content.Context)" /></c>.

 <format type="text/html"><h3>Developer Guides</h3></format></para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">For more information about using NFC, read the
 <format type="text/html"><a href="http://developer.android.com/reference/../guide/topics/nfc/index.html">Near Field Communication</a></format> developer guide.</para>
